Course provides an Overview of the Law of Civil Procedure.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide an understanding of the judicial procedure in civil cases and basic knowledge for successful participation in civil court proceedings and the skills to solve procedural practical problems independently.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has successfully completed the course: 1. can explain the main principles and concepts of civil court proceedings; 2. understands the administration of civil courts and the jurisdiction of courts in resolving civil cases; 3. understands the meaning of procedural time limits and knows how to calculate the time limits; 4. knows the general content and form requirements for procedural documents and knows how to prepare simpler procedural documents; 5. can understand the course of proceedings in the settlement of lawsuits and action-by-petition cases in the county court; 6. is able to present an analysis of the case study of civil court proceedings and a solution; 7. can interpret legal norms of civil court proceedings in accordance with judicial practice.
